<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Product Categories</title>
<style>
  .container {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 300px;
    margin: 50px auto;
  }
  .category-card {
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 30px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .category-icon {
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    margin: 0 auto 20px;
  }
  .category-icon::before {
    content: '';
    border: 1px dashed #e0e0e0;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  }
  .category-icon::after {
    content: '';
    border: 1px dashed #e0e0e0;
    width: 140px;
    height: 140px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  }
  .category-title {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .category-description {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #757575;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
  <h1 class="category-title">Product Categories</h1>
  <div class="category-card">
    <div class="category-icon">
      <img src="icon-placeholder.png" alt="Electronics Icon">
    </div>
    <h2 class="category-title">Electronics & Gadgets</h2>
    <p class="category-description">Discover the latest tech innovations.</p>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
```

Note: Replace "icon-placeholder.png" with the actual icon image you want to use.
